Separators:
In Python, sep is a parameter often used in the print() function. It stands for "separator" and allows you to specify the
 character or string that separates multiple items when they are printed. By default, sep is set to a single
 space character.


 # Using sep to specify a separator between items
print("apple", "banana", "orange", sep=",")  # Output: apple,banana,orange

# You can use any string as a separator
print("one", "two", "three", sep=" *** ")  # Output: one *** two *** three

# You can also specify an empty string as a separator
print("Hello", "world", sep="")  # Output: Helloworld
